Unions Postpone Collective Bargaining Accord to April, Efe Says

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-03-23T17:24:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/unions-postpone-collective-bargaining-accord-to-april-efe-says.html
 Comisiones Obreras and UGT, two
Spanish unions, said they’d seek to reach an agreement on
collective bargaining by the middle of April, Efe newswire
reported today, citing comments from Spanish Labor Minister
Valeriano Gomez.  Both unions still think it’s possible to reach an accord,
which was supposed to happen by March 19, the newswire said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Charles Penty at 
 cpenty@bloomberg.net  